Description:
Rise to the challenge, reap the rewards!
This freestanding weatherboard Victorian home, in liveable condition, offers unlimited potential for renovation and extension (STCA) on a good-sized block with side driveway and private rear garden. Comprising two large double bedrooms, living/dining room, functional kitchen and bathroom/laundry, the home includes period detail and hydronic heating. Here is a great opportunity to create a residence in a developing precinct close to Smith Street cafes, schools, parkland and Collingwood Station.
Insights: 125 Rupert Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
Filled with natural light, this second-floor Islington apartment makes an ideal city pad or welcome addition to any investment portfolio with its impressive dimensions, quality inclusions and secure surrounds. Stylish and serene interior comprises one large bedroom with mirrored robes, central bathroom and spacious open living/dining area leading out to the paved balcony. Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances, as well as heating and cooling, European laundry, intercom/secure entry foyer and lower-level parking space (easy access via Islington Street). On the fringe of East Melbourne, it's walking distance to Victoria Parade trams, Victoria Street/Smith Street restaurants, North Richmond Station, hospital precincts and the open spaces of Fitzroy Gardens. Brilliant!

Description:
Ultra-spacious and secure: immaculate living with panoramic views
What a find! Set to the rear of a well-maintained development with large communal courtyard, this immaculately presented apartment offers secure and private living minutes from Smith Street and Queens Parade cafes, tram routes and freeway access. With views from Studley Park to the CBD and abundant natural light, this stunning residence comprises three well-separated double bedrooms (ensuite and WIR to main), a vast living/dining room flowing to a balcony and full-width entertaining terrace, custom kitchen with premium fittings, stylish main bathroom and euro laundry. Including basement parking/storage and entry security, this prime-value home features loft storage, polished hardwood floors and split-system air conditioning throughout.

Description:
Next-level lifestyle & city skyline views
Apartment 703 - A contemporary Collingwood lifestyle with its eclectic culture and endless cafes is brilliantly complemented by renowned architects Kennedy Nolan with this stunning Haus apartment capturing city skyline views. Showcasing an innovative design where form, function, quality and style are holistically next-level, this impressive apartment is pure inspiration by exciting Smith Street. The streamlined single-level layout features 1 large bedroom with built-in robes, sophisticated living and dining spilling onto a spectacular city-view entertainers' terrace (never better than on NYE!), luxury Neff-appointed stone kitchen, fabulous designer bathroom, European laundry, engineered Oak flooring, reverse-cycle heating/cooling, intercom security plus storage cage and basement car space on title. Footsteps from Melbourne's best array of live music venues, restaurants, fitness venues, coffee roasters, cafes, pubs and retail outlets. Public transport on the doorstep and the CBD only a short walk away.

Description:
Designer indulgence with rooftop terrace panorama
Designed by Architects "Robert Nichol & sons" this magnificent sanctuary boasts a lush vertical garden rising to the rooftop where a spectacular terrace showcases city-to-ranges views. Light and airy with large industrial windows, reclaimed Messmate surfaces and Masson For Light illumination. Drive in and indulge yourself as the internal garage of this captivating warehouse conversion leads directly to a stunning designer space that delivers flexibility, flair and functionality for an amazing city-fringe lifestyle. Features 3 sizable bedrooms, WIR, fitted study/office, versatile rumpus/playroom, upstairs retreat with bi-fold doors to deck, glazed-ceiling dining area, living room with bespoke entertainment unit, Smeg gourmet kitchen, 2 beautiful bathrooms, laundry and heating/cooling. Walk to Gertrude/Smith Streets, Fitzroy Gardens and CBD.

Description:
Work, live, thrive
Featuring a corner position with excellent exposure, this three bedroom period residence + shopfront is a vibrant base for those who'd love to live and work on one site and has potential for dual occupancy. Beyond the spacious and freshly painted shop is a living/meals, with a cosy gas log fire, linked to a kitchen hosting a freestanding stainless steel gas stove. Upstairs, spacious bedrooms offer period features including fireplaces with marble surrounds. There's also a well presented central bathroom, plus an external powder room, polished floorboards and off street parking featuring electronic access. Complete with Commercial 1 zoning (C1Z), it's a stroll to popular Smith Street, trams, trains, Collingwood College, parks, bars and restaurants, and a quick commute to the CBD.

Description:
1 Bedroom + Study at Oxley Apartments!
Ideally located in the heart of vibrant Collingwood lies this exceptionally well maintained one bedroom apartment plus study area. This is the perfect opportunity for the astute investor or first home buyer.
Combining quality finishes with space and an abundance of natural light, this modern and well appointed apartment features large bedroom with built in robes, stylish kitchen with stainless steel appliances, ample pantry and storage space, sleek bathroom, open living and dining space leading to a huge private balcony.
Additional features include split system heating/cooling, secure undercover car space on title, large storage cage, secure video intercom entry large communal BBQ area and swimming pool.
This generously proportioned property has all the hallmarks for exceptional modern living.
This property is also enhanced by its premier inner city local just moments from brilliant Smith St and Gertrude St restaurants and cafes, the CBD, transport and so much more!

Description:
Waiting to shine in vibrant locale
Moments to thriving Smith Street, cafes, restaurants, bars and transport, this three bedroom plus study Victorian offers a brilliant opportunity to make your mark in a hot locale. Block fronted, the residence has a central lounge, kitchen/meals with gas stove and rear courtyard. Three double bedrooms are linked to the lounge by a traditional hall, and the home exhibits coloured glass, lofty ceilings, ceiling medallions and deep cornices. Head out on foot to enjoy a delicious meal, hours of retail therapy, memorable catch ups with friends or a coffee of the quality that makes Melbourne famous the world over. It won't be hard to imagine how to effect a transformation reflecting your style to capitalise on the attractions of the locale, and the CBD is less than 3 kilometres away.

Description:
STYLISH COLLINGWOOD WAREHOUSE CONVERSION
Nelson Alexander are delighted to offer for Private Sale, this stylish warehouse conversion, located on the ground floor of the former Victorian Distillery Buildings c1860 and positioned in the heart of Collingwood's vibrant arts and fashion precinct. The opportunity to both live and work in such a space is rare, but this property boasts both residential usage rights and a commercial zoning, so is uniquely positioned in this highly sought after precinct.
Boasting a delightful open plan interior layout with tranquil tree lined outlook, polished timber floors, lofty high ceilings, fully appointed kitchen and a stylish modern bathroom with shower, the warehouse is within walking distance to the lifestyle precincts of Smith Street and Gertrude Street.
Key Property features:
* Zoning: Commercial 2
* Floor area: 130sqm (approx)
* Large sub-floor storage area 119sqm (approx)
* 1 off street carpark
* Versatile open plan interior
* Fully equipped kitchen, bathroom and laundry
* Delightful tree lined outlook
* Fantastic location only moments from Smith Street, Gertrude Street, Victoria Parade and Melbourne CBD
* An outstanding opportunity for investors or owner occupiers
* A truly unique property in the heart of this popular and high sought after precinct
* Existing use rights for residential occupation.
For all property enquiries, to request a copy of the Contact/Section 32 or to arrange an inspection, please contact exclusive selling agents Nelson Alexander on 9419 5511.
Insights: 5b/21 Northumberland Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Block of five apartments!
A rare opportunity to secure a substantial block of five apartments, each with its own individual Title but all offered for sale as one lot. All have two bedrooms and car space [three with lock-up garages]. The floor plans are exceptionally spacious with abundant natural light drawn from three sides. Currently returning $90,600 per annum. The location is also ideal. Fifteen minutes from the CBD with all the attractions and amenities of the inner city with-in easy reach. A simple refurbishment will pay an astute investor handsome dividends.

Description:
LONG TERM OWNERS
COMMERCIAL 2 ZONING - WITH CONFIRMATION OF EXISTING USE RIGHTS AS A DWELLING - CITY OF YARRA AS OF 27/ 3/ 2018
Held by the same family since 2001, now the time has come to move on to enjoy the sea and tree change of rural and regional Victoria.
Ideally located between Wellington and Smith Streets, the house in the midst of a nice little row of terraces with ornate lacework on white veranda posts - brick paved front courtyard.
House, with its two long boundary side walls of double brick, and facade and all internal walls weatherboard and veneer. The initial passage with tall ceilings and the 2 front bedrooms enjoy timber floor with carpet, and then the central bathroom to the rear through the kitchen and living room is on concrete flooring. Open fireplaces are in each of the front two bedrooms.
From the centre of the house you can start to look beyond the kitchen to see the real depth in the back yard via the fully glazed back of house - is 144 sqm of land area - with approx 10 metres of deep courtyard beyond the house. The backyard is very private and secure, and large enough to give good options for suited recreation, of pets, family space, gardening, hosting parties.
The home is for Private sale and ready to buy today
CONTACT AGENT FOR ALL FURTHER PARTICULARS, SECTION 32, MORE IMAGES, STATEMENT OF INFORMATION & INSPECTION - 93477677

Description:
Spacious & secure designer studio apartment - Approx. 46 Sqm
Get in on the ground floor and find your feet in the thriving Collingwood market with this brilliant studio apartment in Stoll Long architects' outstanding HAUS. Easy single-level access and excellent security in a boutique complex provide peace of mind for investors and first-home buyers, and when the mood takes you there's loads to explore outside your door including cafes, bars, galleries, Gertrude Street restaurants and nearby Fitzroy Gardens. This fabulous contemporary apartment features versatile living and bedroom space with double-glazed sliders to covered eastside balcony, streamlined stone kitchen (Bosch cooktop, drawer dishwasher, stacks of storage), huge modern bathroom, European laundry, reverse-cycle heating/cooling, video intercom, built-in robes, high ceilings and Oak floors.

Description:
Boutique brilliance in the heart of Collingwood
Designed by Map Architecture in a near new block of only 15 and positioned moments from Smith Street and Gertrude Streets, this north facing corner apartment delivers an outstanding city-edge lifestyle with its open-plan design, secure surrounds and great tree lined streetscape views. Bathed in natural light, the apartment's pristine interior comprises two bedrooms (with robes) (master with ensuite) and central bathroom, well-appointed kitchen with quality appliances and dishwasher, open living/dining area out to a large north facing balcony. Add to this split-system heating and cooling, Euro laundry, intercom entry, plus lift access to secure foyer and car parking. Reside or invest, it is perfect either way. In a great location, you can walk or catch the tram to the CBD, sporting events at the MCG, as well as being close to Melbourne's hospital precinct.

Description:
A stunningly spacious warehouse conversion
BY APPOINTMENT ONLY
This magnificent architect-renovated 4BR residence represents Collingwood living at its stylish best, close to Johnston's Street's thriving cafe scene, Victoria Park Station and parks. Designed for maximum light and retaining authentic industrial detail, it offers expansive living and dining zones, bespoke kitchen with stone benchtops and premium appliances, four well-separated double bedrooms (three with luxury ensuites), study, bathroom and laundry. Including a vast garage accessed from a wide laneway, here is a unique property suitable for work-from-home living (zoned Commercial 1/General Residential). Features: generous storage throughout, polished timber floors and air conditioning.

Description:
Sensational Views
Set in the highly sought Yorkshire Brewery development superbly located within Collingwood’s bustling coffee scene and surrounded by award winning restaurants, this attractive home also offers superb access to public transport into the CBD.
Upon entry you’re greeted with a generous open plan lounge dining area with enviable views over the top of Studley Park out to the Dandenong Ranges. The stylish kitchen includes stone benchtop, LED backdrop lighting and European stainless steel appliances. With functionality a key to modern living this apartment also consists of a built-in study desk, 2nd bedroom with mirrored robes and a master bedroom with private balcony and en-suite bathroom. This energy conscious apartment also takes advantage of recycled grey water system, solar hot water and double glazing.
Adding to the desire of the Yorkshire Brewery, residents also have access to private facilities including roof top terrace and dining area, library, car share and bike share, dry cleaning, gymnasium & guest suites.
For an immediate inspection please contact Patrick on 0402 075 501.

Living the Good Life - Luxury, Lifestyle, Location

Description:
Exclusive inner-city warehouse living
In a unique boutique environment defined by its historic surrounds and exposed industrial elements, this New York-style townhouse delivers a lifestyle of absolute privacy, quality and floorplan flexibility. An abundance of ambient light throughout, the home's bespoke interior comprises 2 bedrooms (extra-large master with modern ensuite), equally-stylish main bathroom, versatile lounge and dining/living spaces complemented by a sleek stone-top kitchen with European appliances. Add to this heating and cooling, hardwood floors, Euro laundry and excellent storage, plus secure entry and undercover parking space. Modern living wrapped in heritage style, Smith Street/Gertrude Street cafes and restaurants, cosmopolitan shopping precincts and city-bound trams are all within easy reach.

Description:
Make a great start! Stylish Victorian, top position
Recently refurbished and filled with light, this classic Victorian residence offers an affordable entry to this popular growth precinct close to Smith Street's vibrant cafes, the 86-tram route, Victoria Park station and Yarra parkland and many more lifestyle attractions. An ideal floorplan comprises two large bedrooms, open plan kitchen with adjacent dining room overlooking a central light court, central bathroom and separate laundry, and a full width living room with a wall of glass opening to a north facing brick-paved courtyard (ROW access) for secluded alfresco entertaining. Perfect for first home buyers and investors, this impressive home features high ceilings with highlight windows, polished timber floors, period detail, built in robes, ample storage and split-system air conditioning. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
